<h1>TradeCalc - Share trading calculator</h1>

<p>This is my little pet side project to implement Daryl Guppy's trade
calculations spreadsheet as a web application.</p>

<h2>What's a "trade calculator"?</h2>

<p>You're imagining a calculator right now, with buttons, and a screen, which you
use for adding/subtracting/dividing/etc, aren't you. Probably something like
this:</p>

<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/twylo/1388765993/" title="HP 35 Calculator by Twylo, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1122/1388765993_6e9e3fc098_m.jpg" width="213" height="240" alt="HP 35 Calculator"></a>

<p><strong>Well, that's pretty much exactly what this <em>isn't</em>!</strong></p>

<p>TradeCalc is a simple tool for share traders to help calculate the potential <strong>risk</strong>,
and <strong>profitability</strong>, of buying <strong>shares</strong>.</p>

<p>It <strong>does not</strong> help you calculate your <em>stop
loss</em> or your <em>target exit</em> price, but once you have those
numbers, it will calculate how much <strong>risk</strong> a trade exposes you to, and
how much you can <strong>profit</strong> from it.</p>

